  "local_port": 42116,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you check an AT&T balance?",
  "response": "To check your AT&T account balance, you can use several methods. Here\u2019s a list of common ways:\n\n### 1. **AT&T Website:**\n   - **Log In:** Go to [AT&T's official website](https://www.att.com/).\n   - **Access My Account:** Click on the \"Account\" or \"My AT&T\" link.\n   - **View Balance:** Log in with your AT&T credentials to see your account balance and other details.\n\n### 2. **AT&T Mobile App:**\n   - **Download**: If you haven\u2019t already, download the myAT&T app from the Apple App Store or Google Play Store.\n   - **Log In:** Open the app and log in using your AT&T account credentials.\n   - **Check Balance:** Navigate to the section that displays your account balance and billing information.\n\n### 3. **Text Message:**\n   - **Dial:** Send a text message with the word \"BAL\" or \"BALANCE\" to \u201c*BAL\u201d (225).\n   - **Receive:** You should receive a text message back with your current balance.\n\n### 4. **Phone Call:**\n   - **Dial:** Call AT&T customer service at 1-800-288-2020.\n   - **Follow Automated Instructions:** Follow the prompts to get information about your account balance.\n   - **Speak to a Representative:** Optionally, you can speak to an AT&T representative for more detailed inquiries.\n\n### 5. **USSD Code (Prepaid Service):**\n   - **Dial:** Dial *777# from your AT&T prepaid phone.\n   - **Receive:** You will receive a message with your balance information.\n\n### 6. **Billing Statement:**\n   - **Check Recent Bill:** Review your latest billing statement for the account balance. Statements are often accessible online in your account or can be mailed to you.\n\n### 7. **AT&T Store:**\n   - **Visit a Store:** You can visit an AT&T retail store and ask a representative to check your balance for you.\n\nUsing the above methods, you can quickly check your AT&T balance and manage your account effectively.",
